## Prompts

1. What did you learn this week?    
   > I learned about OCSP and CRL and when to use each. I also learned when to renew vs replace a certificate, when to revoke one, how to check if a certificate is expired, and what can happen if there’s no monitoring in place.

2. What concept was most challenging?  
   > Understanding the difference between soft fail vs hard fail took more time for me to fully understand.

3. Where does this concept appear in real-world systems?  
   > This appears in real-world systems like websites, enterprise networks, and secure applications where certificates are used for HTTPS, authentication, and encryption.

4. How would you explain this topic to a non-technical audience?  
   > I would compare it to an ID or driver’s license. If it’s expired, it’s no longer trusted. Systems check if it’s still valid, just like someone checking an ID, and if it’s not, access is denied.

5. What questions remain?  
   > Who determines and what methods are used to determine how long a certificate is valid for?

